  "instructions": [
    "Heat coconut oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chicken and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the pot and set aside.",
    "Add the onion and garlic to the pot and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the bay leaves, black peppercorns, vinegar, water, fish sauce, salt, and sugar to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Return the chicken to the pot and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Add the chili peppers and tomatoes to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, about 25 minutes.",
    "Stir in the chopped cilantro and serve hot.",
    "Season with additional salt and pepper to taste, if needed."
